---
description: Performance and technical SEO constraints for the Uni Lions public site
alwaysApply: false
globs:
  - "src/**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,css,scss,html}"
  - "public/**/*"
---

performance-seo:
- Protect LCP by prioritizing the actual hero asset and avoiding unnecessary blocking resources.
- Reserve media dimensions and prevent CLS.
- Avoid heavy animation libraries for simple transitions.
- Compress and serve responsive images in modern formats when the stack supports them.
- Avoid duplicate script loading and duplicate analytics initialization.
- Use descriptive title, meta description, canonical URL, Open Graph, and social image.
- Preserve crawlable text and links.
- Add structured data only for content visibly present and factually verified.
- Validate Organization and program/event/course markup against current Google guidance before release.
- Do not add hidden SEO copy or misleading structured data.
